  "body": "# Issue: Default limits are set for log file retention for age and number of logfiles\r\n\r\nIt appears currently a (arbitrary) limit on the age and number of logfiles is hardcoded when logging to files. Hence node logs may be unintentionally deleted (see relevant lines in code below) if the user is not aware. Given that logfiles can prove invaluable for identifying issues this default behavior should probably be changed.\r\nhttps://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon/blob/3c2b99e19c98ebe1ad55b9d25c7660b6704a6b0b/turbo/logging/logging.go#L177-L182\r\n\r\n## Possible Solutions:\r\n* Use default values of 0 (no limit) for MaxAge and MaxBackups\r\n* Make these limits more explicit in the documentation so the user is aware of them\r\n* Expose these parameters in the CLI so that the user can set them themself\r\n",
